                @lang('public.When you interact with our service through various social media, such as when you connect through Facebook or when you like or post a comment on our Facebook page or interact with us on other social media, we may receive information from the social network, such as your profile information, profile photo, username, user ID associated with your social media account, age range, language, country, friends list, and any other information that you allow the social network to share with third parties. The data we receive depends on your privacy settings on the social network. The processing of this information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR) and consent (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR). For more information, see our Facebook privacy policy.')

              </p>
              <br />
              <p>
                <strong
                  >@lang('public.• Contact information about our offers.')</strong
                >@lang('public.You can find on our website forms to leave us your contact information (name, email and telephone number) and receive information about our services. This contact information is stored in our database and in external KnockKnock tools for one year. After this period, the information is anonymous. We process your information as part of KnockKnocks legitimate interest to provide you with the best service within the platform (GDPR article 6 (1) (f)). Note: If you are also registered as a user on the platform, your information will be stored in KnockKnock (article 6 (1) (b) of the Data Protection Law) (GDPR article 6 (1) (f) Protection Law of data).')
              </p>
              <br />

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.2. EXCHANGE AND DISCLOSURE OF INFORMATION')</h3>
              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.reservation, certain data is shared between users, such as their name, email and mobile phone number. Yeah you rent a product, we also share your license number drive with the product owner. Your address is It will be included in the rental agreement that is completed together with the product owner before the start of the. In case of additional costs or accidents related to a reservation of rent, your address can be shared with the owner of the product if the product is registered as a business owner and use your own debt collection service or insurance rent. If you rent your product, we also share the number registration number and the address of the product provided when uploading it. we share billing or payment information with others users.')
                    @lang('public.• Share between users.')</strong>@lang('public.When one is made')

              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• Share within the company')</strong>
                @lang('public.Your data may be shared internally with the company KnockKnock, Gomore ApS or one of its subsidiaries in support of upcoming or previously resolved transactions on the platform.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong
                  >@lang('public.• Profiles, trips and rentals offered and other public information.') </strong
                >@lang('public.Portions of your public profile page, such as your first name and last initial, personal description, education, occupation, age, and average platform response time are publicly visible to other users. If you rent your product or offer a ride on our platform, information related to your trip or product will be publicly available. The transportation or rental list pages will also display some information about you, including your name, car registration number, average response time and acceptance fee (rental only), and age. If you delete information you have posted to KnockKnock, copies may remain viewable in cached and archived pages, or if other users have copied or saved that information. After completing a reservation, users can write comments and rate each other. Reviews are part of your public profile page.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong
                  >@lang('public.• Insurance providers, renting and debt collection.') </strong
                >@lang('public.KnockKnock may share your personal information, including name, address, mobile phone number, email, social security or national identity number, and information about your rental, rideshare, or leasing activity on KnockKnock. These service providers provide services on our behalf or otherwise assist in providing the service to you. KnockKnock may also request and receive from these service providers information about the status of your payment, pending payment or debt collection.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• External alliances.')</strong>
                @lang('public.We may share your name, email, phone number, and rental, ridesharing, or leasing activity on the Platform, in partnership with outside companies to provide you with additional KnockKnock-related services, for example, vouchers for soda at a gas station or a discount at a car wash.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• Data analysis tools.')</strong>
                @lang('public.We may share information about your use of the Platform with third party analytics that allow us to understand how users interact with the product, as well as target KnockKnock marketing communication that we send to you.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• Widgets and Aggregators.') </strong>
                @lang('public.In order to increase the chances of obtaining a reservation, we may display parts of the KnockKnock platform (for example, your transport or rental offer) on sites operated by KnockKnocks business partners, including technologies such as widgets or API connections. If your trip or rental is displayed on a partners site, information from their public profile page may also be displayed.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• Security and compliance with the law.') </strong>
                @lang('public.We may also share personal information if necessary to comply with any applicable law or regulation or to enforce our Terms and Conditions, including the investigation of any violation or suspected criminal behavior.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.• Aggregate data.') </strong>
                @lang('public.We may also aggregate and anonymize your personal information and share that anonymous and/or aggregated information with third parties. This information is not personally identifiable and is used for industry and market analysis, demographic profiling, marketing and advertising, and other business purposes.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.3. OTHER IMPORTANT INFORMATION')</h3>
              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.3.1. Analysis of your communications')</strong>
                @lang('public.We may review or analyze your communications (including messages sent to other users, comments included in trip or rental descriptions, and profile page content) on the platform for fraud prevention, risk assessment, compliance regulatory, research, product development, research and customer support. The processing of your personal data in this regard is based on our legitimate interest in the development of our products, research and customer support (article 6 (1) (f) of the GDPR and to comply with our legal obligations (article 6 (1) (c) of GDPR).')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.3.2. Data retention')</strong>
                @lang('public.Your user data will be keep while your account is active, as they are necessary to complete the us s public profile, are used to facilitate a booking transaction or are necessary for the purposes risk and insurance. When you close your account, we will delete your user data six months after the closure of the account, to unless you have outstanding payments or we have considered necessary to keep your data for reasons related to risks, insurance or criminal investigations. The messages that you send to another user on the platform will be kept as long as your account is active. Messages will be retained for a period of 6 months after the closure of the account. This is for ensure that we still have the ability to help with any complaints, insurance cases, or criminal investigations related to a previous reservation. If you want to remove specific information shared with another user before the deletion period ends, contact us by email with a request in which specify what information you want to remove. We will remove the information as soon as possible, and in any case not more than 30 days after receipt of a valid application by written. We reserve the right to refuse removal if the removal request is related to a claim active or potential customer, insurance case, or criminal investigation. Contact details are in the section 7 ("Contact").')

              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.3.3. Google Maps')</strong>
                @lang('public.Some parts of the KnockKnock platform use Google Maps, including the Google Maps APIs. Use of Google Maps is subject to the Google Maps Additional Terms of Use and Googles Privacy Policy.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.4. YOUR CHOICES')</h3>
              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.4.1. Access and update')</strong>
                @lang('public.You can review and change your account information at any time by logging into your account and reviewing your account settings and user profile.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.4.2. communications')</strong>@lang('public.You can choose not to receive')

                >@lang('public.SMS and send notifications on your mobile phone from your account settings. You can also opt out of receiving notification emails from KnockKnock that relate to receiving messages from other users, reservation requests, matches for travel alerts. If you receive our marketing newsletter, you can unsubscribe using the unsubscribe link in the message or in your account settings.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <p>
                <strong>@lang('public.4.3. Review and delete your information')</strong>
                @lang('public.You may request in writing copies of your personal information in our possession. We will provide you with a copy of the personal information in our possession as soon as possible, and in any event no later than 30 days after receiving a valid written request. We may request proof of identification to verify your identity and validate the request. If your personal information that we hold is inaccurate, please let us know and we will update the relevant information. You can also request the deletion of your personal data in accordance with the relevant data protection legislation. We will notify you within 30 days of your valid request of the relevant action taken.')
              </p>

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.5. SECURITY')</h3>
              <p>@lang('public.We are continually implementing and updating our security measures to help protect your information from unauthorized access. Specifically, we do the following to protect you:')
              </p>
              <br />
              <p>@lang('public.Before storing your password, we apply a cryptographically secure hashing algorithm to it. This means that even if data is stolen from our servers, your password is safe.')
              </p>
              <br />
              <p>@lang('public.We only use industry standard encryption algorithms and well tested code libraries. Our database, as well as all of our application servers, are powered by Amazon Web Services (AWS), and we rely on Amazons infrastructure and physical security measures.')
              </p>

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.6. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY')</h3>
              <p>@lang('public.We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy or related procedures at any time in accordance with this provision. We will post the updated Privacy Policy on the KnockKnock Platform and update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. Changes to KnockKnocks privacy policy are effective when posted on this page. Your continued use of the KnockKnock services after these changes means that you accept the revised Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these changes, you may choose to close your account with us.')
              </p>

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.7. CONTACT')</h3>
              <p>@lang('public.If you have any questions or complaints about this Privacy Policy or about KnockKnocks information handling practices, you may contact us at:')
              </p>
              <strong>@lang('public.Olatz Rivera Olmedo')</strong>
              <a href="">Info.knock.sport@gmail.com</a>
              <p>@lang('public.You can file a claim with the competent control authority if you consider that our processing of your personal data violates the applicable data legislation. Contact details for all EU Supervisory Authorities can be found here.')
              </p>
              <br />

              <h3 id="h3">@lang('public.8. GDPR POLICY')</h3>
              <p>@lang('public.This policy informs you about the data processing that we carry out when you contact KnockKnock by telephone. At KnockKnock we value the trust of Users and their privacy, and for this reason we explain below how we treat your data. If you have any questions or want to receive more information in this regard, you can write to us at')
                <strong>[info.knock.sport@gmail.com].</strong>
              </p>

              <h4 id="h4">
                @lang('public.WHO IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE PROCESSING OF YOUR DATA?')
              </h4>
              <p>@lang('public.The data controller is the one who decides the purpose for which your personal data is used, in this case, Olatz Rivera Olmedo. with DNI 79068106V and registered office at [Calle Batalla de Arapiles 4, Escalera Derecha, 2D 50004 Zaragoza] You can contact our privacy manager at the following email:')
                <strong><a href=""></a>[olatz.rivera.olmedo@gmail.com]</strong>
              </p>
              <br />
              <h4 id="h4">@lang('public.WHAT DATA DO WE PROCESS?')</h4>
              <p>@lang('public.The personal data that we process comes from the information that you provide us as a User in the telephone conversations that you have with KnockKnock when you need us to manage any query or request, you want to answer questions or obtain information about our services or we offer you new products, services and offers or promotions on those you have already purchased. We only collect the necessary data for each purpose. Keep in mind that, if you do not provide the mandatory information, we may not be able to attend to your query or request or manage the treatment.')
              </p>
              <br />
              <h4 id="h4">@lang('public.FOR WHAT PURPOSE DO WE PROCESS YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND WHAT IS THE LEGITIMATION FOR THE PROCESSING OF YOUR DATA?')
S?
              </h4>
              <p>@lang('public.Your personal data will be processed for: a. Manage queries or requests received, based on your consent. b. Provide our customer service (solve incidents and doubts you have had when using KnockKnock products, such as shared trips, rentals between individuals or renting), either at your request or because of our need for service management. The basis of legitimacy in these cases will be your consent or the contractual relationship you have with us. c. Make recommendations on improvements and optimization of the use of our services, such as improvements that you can make in the user profile to increase your rental requests, offer you the installation of keyless devices, renew your rental contract or offer you the possibility of improving the contracted products, based on your consent. d. Send you promotions and offers about our services, based on your consent.')

              </p>
              <p>@lang('public.and. Control of calls received on billing and management of users, for security purposes, based on the relationship contractual agreement that you have with us and/or based on our legitimate interest in guaranteeing the security of the information and respect for confidentiality by our staff. F. Control of the quality of telephone services and training of personnel in charge of them, based on the consent given or to the legitimate interest of KnockKnock to constantly improve telephone service to use ')
.
              </p>

              <br />

              <h4 id="h4">@lang('public.FOR HOW LONG WILL WE KEEP YOUR DATA?')</h4>
              <p>@lang('public.Your personal data will be kept for the necessary period for the purpose for which they were collected, and specifically: a. In relation to the attention of queries and requests and with the provision of customer service, will be kept as long as it is necessary to attend to the query and manage the petition. b. In connection with the making of recommendations or improvements and offers, the data will be processed until you object to the treatment or request the deletion of your personal data. c. Regarding security, for the duration of your relationship as client or supplier or until they are made periodically quality supervisions. d. Regarding the control of quality, will be kept until the sessions of supervision and training, and for a maximum of [12] months in If you are not a registered KnockKnock user. if you already have an account at KnockKnock we will keep them for as long as have your account active + 12 months Once the data stops if necessary for the purpose for which we treat them, will remain blocked for the sole purpose of attending to any liability or obligations that may arise from the treatment of them.')

              </p>
              <br />

              <h4 id="h4">@lang('public.TO WHICH RECIPIENTS WILL YOUR DATA BE COMMUNICATED?')</h4>
              <p>@lang('public.Your data may be communicated to service providers who  help us to carry out our activity, for example, IT tools, verification or monitoring, technical support services, etc. some of which have processing or support centers located outside Space European Economic (EEA). We guarantee that when your data could leave the EEA, they will maintain the same level of protection based on compliance with the provisions set forth in the European data protection regulations. In this sense, the international data transfers will be made (i) to countries with an adequate level of protection declared by the European Commission (ii) based on the provision of guarantees appropriate (standard contractual clauses or corporate rules binding), or (iii) by virtue of the authorization of the competent control authority or other cases provided for in the normative. To receive more information about the international data transfers or obtain confirmation or copy of the guarantees used, you can contact us at the addre')')

                <strong> [gdpr@KnockKnock.com].</strong>
              </p>
              <h4 id="h4">@lang('public.WHAT ARE YOUR RIGHTS?')</h4>
              <p>@lang('public.As the owner of your personal information, you can request confirmation of whether your personal data is being processed and, if so, access them. You can too request the rectification of inaccurate data or, where appropriate, request its deletion when, among other reasons, the data is no longer are not necessary for the purposes for which they were collected. In certain circumstances, it is possible to request the limitation of the processing of your data, in which case only the We will keep for the exercise of actions or the defense of claims. You can revoke at any time the consents given. Once the revocation has been exercised, which will not have retroactive character except legal provision that imposes said character, your data may be kept blocked during the prescription periods established by the applicable regulations. Remember that you can also oppose the processing of your data, particularly regarding communications commercial, in which case we will not process the data, except for compelling legitimate reasons or for the exercise or defense of possible claims. To exercise the aforementioned rights, write to our privacy officer, attaching a copy of document proving your identity, to any of the following address')

                <strong>
                  [info.knock.sport@gmail.com o
                  olatz.rivera.olmedo@gmail.com]</strong
                >.
              </p>
              <p>@lang('public.To help us process your request, we ask you to indicate “Data Protection” in the subject line.')

              </p>
              <p>@lang('public.Likewise, if you have any doubt regarding the exercise of,your rights, before going to the Control Authority, you,We remind you that, if you wish, you can contact us directly,by writing to our privacy officer and we will try to,help you in the best possible way. Finally, we remind you,that you have the right to file a claim with the authority,competent in matters of data protection (in Spain,,www.aepd.es) in case you have knowledge or consider that,an event may imply a breach of the regulations,applicable in terms of data protection.')

              </p>
